description.narrative: Newborns and mothers, especially from the most vulnerable governorates and in humanitarian situations have increased access to quality Maternal,which contributes to Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, all newborns, children, adolescents and women in Iraq access and equitably use affordable, high-impact health and nutrition services, especially the most vulnerable in humanitarian situations.
